5:
Our client says that, a few days ago, 
she was attacked by a dragon in these 
woods.
6:
She claims it was of a vicious breed... 
but I would not trust fully to the 
evaluation of a layperson.
9:
Roger that.
...And can I just say, I never thought 
YOU would invite US dragon-hunting.
12:
Agreed. This seems wholly inconsistent 
with accounts of you being 
overprotective.
15:
...I'd wager all those accounts came 
from Nimbus.
17:
Well, my eyes have been opened. I see 
now that Alk is a fine warrior.
24:
Furthermore, this was a quest I felt you 
two needed to be a part of.
32:
You will see soon enough.
En garde!
49:
We won't break through her defenses 
like this...
Alk, get back!
73: She was just protecting her egg...
76:
You will not lay so much as a finger on 
my child!
79:
You do not belong here. You must find 
someplace else to live.
81: I do not belong? I was BORN here!
82:
I will not be banished by lowly 
humans!
84: It's the only way to save your child.
88:
Yeeeah... Sorry, Azel, but I don't want to 
fight anymore.
91:
Is that so?
Well, it seems I have nothing left to 
teach you.
94:
Dragon! It is as the girl says. If you 
wish to keep your child from harm, you 
must leave these woods!
104:
This is your last warning. Leave these 
woods!
108:
Further north, there is a mountain 
range. Cross over it, and you will be in 
a wild realm inaccessible to humans. 
A suitable place to raise your child in 
peace.
112:
But should you choose war, I will fell 
you here and now.
You can only have one, Dragon. Pride... 
or the life of your child.
114:
Gr... GRAAAH! I shall never forget this... 
Mark my words!
117: Alk, do you have a large cloth?
123: We can wrap the egg in it.
126:
Oh! Okay, yeah, uh... Maybe we should 
fill it with grass first, you know, give it 
some padding.
132: We were totally the bad guys here.
135:
As soon as we threatened her with 
brute force, we ceased being 
negotiators and became... tyrants.
138:
Yes... But it is still an improvement 
from the dark days of mindless 
slaying.
142:
But I thought dragon slaying was your 
life.
145:
It was. Once. But then I learned that 
even humans and dragons may come 
to an understanding.
151:
A dragon taught me. A noble... and 
beautiful dragon.
152:
Today, I sought to pass her lesson on 
to the two of you, but... it seems I didn't 
need to.
154:
You are blinkered neither by ego nor 
prejudice. You see things far more 
clearly than I ever could.
157:
Gee... Thanks. But I still feel like I'm 
getting schooled by Light and Stella 
every day.
160: It was an honor to meet ALL of you.
164:
Alk. Stella. I swear, here and now, on 
my pride as a dragon slayer, that, 
together, we shall build a new future!
